A few pics from finally installing my "tuckin brakes" kit from @downstar that I've literally held onto for years. Never had a reason to break down the brakes until now, but I always planned on doing it. I'm running a Wilwood 1.125 compact master cylinder (which requires a wilwood specific clevis sold separately) , downstar brake booster delete plate, and of course the downstar soft line brake it. 

All lines were the perfect length for an easy install. Took me awhile to cut and flare my rear brake lines due to getting a 45° flare tool initially and having to wait awhile for the correct 37° flare tool from Rigid. (Which I highly recommend btw). Weighing my options and trying not to overthink the setup. Considering making use of a larger sized tucked radiator for use with an intercooler, or I may just stick to the popular intercooler radiator combos that use something that's the same size as my Rywire radiator.  This larger one is the same 24" wide, and 3" thick dual core dual pass, but it's just under 12" tall as opposed to 9" tall. It also has a larger shroud and 10" fans, compared to 8" Derale fans. 

My Rywire radiator never had a problem keeping things cool down here in Texas, but I'm wondering if I should go bigger as a " just in case " sort of thing. *short vid coming soon, gotta edit the clips together *
